    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Christiern Winther [?] to Miklós Oláh (Leuven, 24 March
                    1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Oláh is toiling every day to make sure he supports as
                            many people as possible; he has people within his household who want to
                            reciprocate Oláh’s good deeds with their diligence and tirelessness. It
                            is no wonder that the Queen entrusts her secrets to such an excellent
                            person, the dignity of whose mind is solid and unflinching. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Christiernus Umbra Cymber<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1"
                        >Probably Christiern Winther, see <hi rend="smallcap">Tournoy</hi> 2015,
                        527; and <hi rend="smallcap">Christiansen</hi> 2002, 82.</note> Nicolao Olao
                    suo salutem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Quamquam praeclari ingenii tui dexteritas mira quadam morum
                    maturitate unita, tum aetas, quae et ipsa iam quoque maturuit, palam arguunt et
                    perspicue, te viri consummati, ita circulum absolvisse, ut nulla aut vix ulla
                    iam amplius quaeat fieri accessio, nihilominus adeo otium non amplecteris, quin
                    honestissimis studiis intentus, contendas quotidie te ipsum, si fieri possit,
                    superare, tanquam <persName>Neoptolemus</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.2">He was Achilles’ son.</note> quispiam Martis et militiae
                    ignarus, arma manibus diurnis nocturnisque vigilans versare solet, ne rudis in
                    harena cum hoste <choice>
                        <orig>congredietur</orig>
                        <supplied>congrediatur</supplied>
                    </choice> turpiter succubiturus. Quae res vel hoc argumento abunde claret, Vir
                    virtute Ornatissime, quod intra parietes domesticos a latere habeas ac foveas,
                    qui quaeunt sua vigilantia atque industria, tuas dotes alioqui ditissimas
                    ditiores reddere, pro quorum salute exacto anno, ut audio, non parum sollicitus
                    sudasti, quo nomine ex professo famulum me tibi invenias devinctiorem. Tum usus
                    et litteratorum necessitudo accedit, quam huic negotio impense conferre, vel
                        <quote xml:id="quote.1">talpae appareat.</quote><note type="quote"
                        xml:id="note.quote.1">Cf. Erasm. <hi rend="italic">Adag</hi>. 255. I, III,
                        55. Talpa caecior; and 3571. IV, VI, 71. Loquax talpa.</note> In primis
                        <persName>Cornelii Sceperi</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.3"
                        >Cornelis de Schepper.</note> viri et singularis prudentiae et doctrinae
                    undevis exquisitissimae, qui haud dubie divino ingenio donatus, tum facundiae
                    flumine <milestone unit="pb"/>iuxta praeditus, omnium de se opinione aut est
                    superior, aut genius parum propitius, nobis tenebras ob oculos offuderit, unde
                    indicitum caliginem contraxerit. Ad hoc mare felicitatis, tamquam quaedam
                    auctaria, adfluunt felicissimae dotes, quas in ista generosa <choice>
                        <orig>monte</orig>
                        <supplied>mente</supplied>
                    </choice> deprehendi, quae ulla oblivione e mea memoria non poterunt facile
                    intercipi. Nempe candor, ingenii canities, humanitas, venustas, gravitas, quae
                    te heroi affinem facit, quibus omnibus veluti anteambulonibus et pedissequis
                    quibusdam uteris familiariter, ut minime mirum sit, si princeps illustrissima
                    talem sibi delegerit, ac sua arcana concredierit sapientissime. Huiusmodi
                    viatica, patria viduata ab hostibus, tecum hospes absportas, quem quamvis
                    hostilis tyrannus violenta manu bonorum fortuitorum bona parte dispoliarit, tuae
                    tamen mentis sublimitas eis fortunae fluctibus manet semper inconcussa atque
                    immersabilis, nec unquam labascit, aut victa infringitur nihilomagis, <quote
                        xml:id="quote.2">quam Marpesia cautes,</quote><note type="quote"
                        xml:id="note.quote.2">Verg. <hi rend="italic">Aen</hi>. VI,471.</note> undis
                    undique insultantibus quassa commovetur. </p>
                <quote xml:id="quote.3">
                    <lg xml:id="lg.1">
                        <l xml:id="l.1">Has tu reliquias retines a caede tuorum,</l>
                        <l xml:id="l.2">quas non saeva manus, non mille hostilia tela</l>
                        <l xml:id="l.3">Turcarumve cohors adimit tibi, turba cruenta,</l>
                        <l xml:id="l.4">nec fortuna potens, potis est auferre beatus</l>
                        <l xml:id="l.5">quo minus eis ducibus divos confisus adibis</l>
                        <l xml:id="l.6">famaque post fatum non interitura manebis.</l>
                    </lg>
                </quote>
                <note type="quote" xml:id="note.quote.3">It is probably a poem by Winther, but it
                    has not been confirmed.</note>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Vale, Nicolae Generosissime, nec credas Colacem<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.4">Colax was the title of pieces written by Ennius and Plautus.
                        The name means ‘flatterer’.</note> quempiam adulari, ut ventri prospectum
                    sit. Nam <choice>
                        <orig>ταῦτην τῆν</orig>
                        <supplied>ταύτην τὴν</supplied>
                    </choice> γραφὴν σου<note type="critic" xml:id="note.5">‘this writing of
                        yours’.</note> a viris multo emunctissimae naris accepi. Dominum
                        <persName>Cornelium Sceperum</persName>, quo cum per otium etiam litteris
                    nugabor, ex me saluta et nostra nugamenta boni consule. Iterum vale. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Lovanii</placeName> ex aedibus <persName>Rutgeri
                        Rescii</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">Rutger Ressen.</note>
                    XXIIII. Martii anno MDXXXV.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
